FT  13 OCT 92 / International Company News: General Motors averts strike
GENERAL MOTORS and the United Auto Workers Union have reached an agreement
to avert a strike at a key parts plant at Anderson, Indiana, Reuter reports.
The plant, part of the US carmaker's Inland Fisher Guide division, supplies
exterior lighting and bumpers for virtually all of the company's North
American assembly plants.
GM said it had agreed to add 240 jobs to the plant over a two-year period.
